title: Not a great marketplace for watches
reviewText: I've purchased several and sold a couple of watches on this site but think the last transaction may be my last.  Their site causes regular credit cards to reject the order for fraud purposes initially.  Once you've alerted your bank that it's a legitimate transaction there is no one from their team you can talk to to "update payment information" per their request so that a transaction can go through.  I lost one purchase on this basis. For another purchase, I was charged but then within 5 minutes, I was refunded my money and the order was cancelled.   StockX explained that the seller was problematic but I then had the transaction for a luxury watch on my account all week before I was refunded.  Shouldn't the company have prevented the seller from listing in the first place or verifying before running my card?In both cases, their customer service was terrible and it took a long time to receive a basic and not helpful answer.

title: Beware!!
reviewText: I purchased a pair of shoes that I already own. I wanted a second pair because I proposed to my wife in them and I wanted a brand new pair just to keep fresh. They were a European release only and when I received them, the box labels were a bit off and the shoe had Chinese size stickers. They did not look like the pair that I had which I got from an authorized retailer. I emailed them about it and sending them pictures and they didn't address my concern. I reached out three times and without a response that addressed my concern, I disputed the transaction with PayPal. StockX then emailed me immediately telling me to send the shoes back. They then suspended my account indefinitely. I kept emailing them saying this wasn't a fair justification of suspending my account. Before this incident, I have sold over 60 shoes and purchased several on this platform however, it seems they only want to protect their image and not take ownership of letting a fake pair slip through the cracks.

Ive been trying to contact stockx but with an nonexistent customer service, it's impossible to reach out to them. Theres no number, no lack of concern or any form of protection for the items we are buying. I didnt even once get an email w an explanation as to why shipping took so long. It took 3 emails & 2 days to finally get a response only to have their joke of a team tell me I need to contact ups & that it is now their concern not stockx's. At an outrageous 15% of a buying transaction fee & i cant even get any of the basic compartments of a company to ensure I received my products? With that being said, after the data breach on the accounts, ive gotten shady text messages about items offered for sale with the person sharing my information about who i am & what i was previously bidding on their app & how they now have it for sale for cheaper than stockx had. Ive received numerous phone calls & had to change more than enough of my personal data that i had trusted a large enough company such as stockx to keep secure. PLEASE STAY OFF THE APP. ITS NOTHING BUT A SCAM & IT WONT STOP UNTIL WE TAKE OUR BUSINESS TO A BETTER COMPANY SUCH AS GOAT.

title: Selling ok, DO NOT BOTHER BIDDING OR BUYING
reviewText: I have sold one pair of sneakers and it went fine, however, I have won two bids on Nike x  Off White collaborations (Air Max 97 Black & Vapormax Black) and both orders were cancelled due to issues with the seller, so I did not get either pair. After a week of the first sale not shipping and after multiple contacts with StockX (while being told to be patient and sip a daiquiri), the order was cancelled. I really wanted to purchase the sneakers and the price had gone up. I tried multiple times to see if anything could be done and I was basically told "StockX is a marketplace and is not responsible for orders that are cancelled". No sneakers, no discounts and because this happened a second time, I WILL NOT BE BUYING SNEAKERS FROM STOCKX. I had active bids on 5 sneakers and I have taken them all down. In addition, I have also read on other reviews that people have made and they have not received the additional shoelaces with their StockX purchases (as the sellers are not required to send them), which can be a big hit if you spend a lot on an Nike x Off White Collaboration (the laces can sell for +$50). I would rather pay a little more money on another site and ensure I'm getting everything rather than get my order cancelled AGAIN and possibly not get extra laces.

title: Sell at your own risk!
reviewText: I listed and sold a brand new, never been worn or washed, Frozen yellow Yeezy shirt.  I carefully folded and packed it in a box, putting bubble wrap on top so it wouldn't wrinkle and then shipped it right away for authentication.  Days later I received an email saying it didn't pass authentication and that I would be charged $13.95 to have it sent back to me. I immediately asked to have someone call me and provided them the original receipt from Yeezy Supply for the shirt (which including all the other items I purchased at the time). They did not returned my shirt back to me in the same condition I sent it in. They jammed it into a large envelope by rolling it up tight, smashing the packing slip in the shirt. Sleeves were folded the shirt was so wrinkled it looked like it was thrown into a bin. Loose turquoise string and lint all over it.  I'm appalled by the horrible customer service and lack of professionalism.  I have already pulled all my other listed items and will use another resell platform. ***Be wary of celebrity endorsements... they probably pay them and the experience they have will not be the same as yours or mine.

title: FIRST TIME BUYER...NOT HAPPY!
reviewText: I've heard great things about StockX by multiple people and thought I'd try out their app and purchase a pair of shoes that I've really been wanting! I got a pretty good deal! (Although sales tax and shipping is a Bi$$$h!) I ordered on Valentines Day, 2/14/2020. Shortly after placing my order I received a confirmation email with a time tracker that said, "ordered, shipped to StockX, verified and shipped, and delivered." The "ordered" slot was now check marked. The next email I received wasn't until 2/21/2020, saying, Your order is en route to StockX for verification. You can expect to receive it around 02/25/2020 - 02/27/2020. Now the "shipped to StockX" slot was check marked. Cool. So I wait patiently for my next update. 2/25 comes and goes, nothing. 2/26 passes, and there's still no check mark on the "verified and shipped" slot. Nor have I gotten any new emails. Hmm...? I don't know where they ship from, but I figured at that point there was no way I'd receive it on time! So it's now 2/27 and I email StockX support at this point wondering why I haven't received any updates and where my package is. I did get a timely response to my email, stating that my order was already shipped out and delivered the day prior. (2/26) It also included tips on how to locate my missing order. (Irritation sets in)1. I was bothered by the poor grammar in their response email. Totally unprofessional. (But not the main problem) 2. I was told to ask my neighbors, fine, but I was actually offended that I'd be asked to file a police report to send them for the pair of missing shoes that I have still yet to even receive a confirmation for? I'm sorry, does my word mean nothing? I'm reaching out to you guys on the last day of estimated arrival wondering where my confirmation, tracking number, and order is! Furthermore, do our police officers not have better things to do than to come to my house to file a report on a missing shoe box? I had been checking my emails religiously, waiting for any updates on my order, as well as checking on my StockX app that had the same information my last email on 2/21, did! "Shipped to StockX". Not once did an email ever come in to notify me that my shoes were on their way to my house, nor did I even receive an email when the shoes were supposedly "delivered". Furthermore, I work from home, have a guard dog, and a doorbell camera. No one showed up to my door to drop off any packages between 2/25-2/27. I would know.This is my first time ordering from StockX and overall I am truly unsatisfied and completely unhappy! I expected a lot more and was unpleasantly surprised that I spent over $100 on the StockX app and didn't receive better communication, tracking information, more helpful customer service, and the dang shoes I ordered!!! Ugh...I just want my money back at this point!

title: Delivery Time Frame
reviewText: StockX is great company with brilliant ideas. They have made it a even playing field for consumers to purchase exclusive sneakers that are primarily sold out immediately online from Bots and other applications used to control the inventory of highly sought after sneakers. The problem. I have most with stockX is the delivery time frame. Those who's shop at StockX understand the way buying from StockX works. The solution that needs to be put in place immediately is sellers need to send already in possession sneakers into StockX they plan on selling, then hold the sneaker and put it through the authentication process, so when a sneaker is sold all that has to be done is ship the sneaker to the buyer it's pretty simple. I and I'm sure many others don't like to wait and if stockX is going to keep there market share on such a wide open market this change must be implemented quickly. On the lighter note that's my only complaint thus far about StockX.

title: Nice platform with implementation issues
reviewText: Great platform for buying/selling sneakers.  Implementation is a bit rough, however, as there are some data and quality issues.  For example, the highest bid and latest sale is presented on the sneaker main sale screen.  There is a glitch in the detail listing, however, where the bid details will show a number of phantom bids higher than the actual high bid.  If you don't notice you could over bid because of these phantom bids.  Also, the latest sale value glitches on some items showing significantly higher than any current or previous bid ask.  Again, if you're not paying attention this could falsely lead you to bid higher than needed.  Tech help says reinstall app or use desktop but errors still exist.  Also, quality review on older shoes is poor.  So, buyer beware as StockX will hide behind loosely written terms and conditions that do not favor the buyer.  Remember no returns if the quality is poor or it wasn't previously stored well.  All that said, the process of buying, selling, shipping, notifications works really well.  Top notch in this department.

title: Under-promise & over-produce
reviewText: I'm pretty new to StockX... but I can safely say I'm highly impressed and plan to use them in the future. In the last couple of weeks I've made 3 separate purchases. 1 for my son's birthday and 2 for myself. I was nervous after I purchased my son's when I found out it the site said it normally takes 6-10 business days for delivery. Thought for sure my son's shoes weren't going to make it in time with Labor Day weekend being that weekend. But it got to us in 4 business days. My other 2 shoes came way under the promised date as well. Everything was in great shape. I bid on all 3 of my shoes and got all 3 for WAY under retail. I know not all shoes are under retail (some are way over) but I got what I wanted and was pretty happy about it. Highly recommended for any sneakerhead or just your average joe looking for some kicks.

DONT USE STOCKX ITS A WASTE OF TIME!!!!!!!!!

title: Very poor business practices.
reviewText: Won the winning bid on a pair of $300 KD12 90s Kids sneakers on Friday 4/11. It's now Weds 4/17, and their status is still showing "waiting for seller to ship". I understand the weekend fell in the middle, but their own FAQ states that the seller has two (2) days to ship the item. It's now past that point. Stockx doesn't even have an contact telephone number to reach them, so you have to rely on email contact. I received an email from one of their CSR's in reply to my inquiry, and all it consisted of was stating (word for word what their online FAQ states) of taking anywhere from 6-10 business days for normal delivery to me. Nothing said about the delay in receiving the shoes from the seller, how this diverted from their own online statement of the seller having 2 business days to do so, not even a resemblance of care or empathy. Thanks for nothing, Stockx. I'll be sure to take my future business elsewhere, after I try and recoup my $300 from you guys. I urge others to steer WAY clear of this company and use better organized companies out there — which there are a few of, but I won't advertise those here. Just do your homework and read reviews to find the good ones. Stockx clearly isn't one of them! Extremely irritated at this transaction and they could give a rip less after taking your money.

title: Goat is a better option
reviewText: I was super excited when I found out about this app. Their site is actually pretty cool, the way you can search, filter, and scroll through exactly the silhouette that your after. My problem comes with the business side of Stock X. The process takes forever. They don't hold their sellers to the timeline they provide, and when the seller takes forever to ship, you can't cancel your order. They say they'll find you another pair at no cost, but that doesn't help when you've bought a pair as a gift and the seller doesn't ship them for almost a week. If your into the shoe game, try Goat out over StockX, until StockX can enforce their policies a little better, and give the buyer a chance to get out of the deal when the seller doesn't cooperate. I won't buy another pair from StockX again until these issues are resolved.

title: Pros and Cons from my experience
reviewText: Okay first off I would like to say this a good respectable app. I appreciate the fact they go through the lengths of verification. But I do have my cons through my selling experience. As compared to other apps when selling a product the user is able to upload pics of their item so you know exactly what you are purchasing . That is something this app does not have .. a interface for the user to upload "pictures" of actual item. This is important because let's just say the shoes you sell are dang near perfect item except there is a mark or little bit of dirt on the shoe. Typically this is not a big deal but for whatever reason it was for mine. I sold a pair of dang near perfect shoes literally only worn twice and in that time a little dirt on the bottom but far from being damaged. The rubber sole was all intact . So when my sneakers sold they were rejected with the explanation that they only sell deadstock unworn shoes ? Which is fine but if that's the case then only shoes stores should be able to  sell on this app .. because unless you have a perfect shoe that has never been worn or even taken out the box this app is not for you. Which takes back to my point there should be some upload process to at least show the quality of shoe so we are all not wasting time and money spent shipping back and forth. Just for someone to tell you your shoe was rejected because a piece of lint was on it . Thanks but i most likely will not use this app. Good app but just not for me. There are other selling platforms that cater directly to the user not the hype of appearance

title: Sellers Beware
reviewText: I've sold on this platform consecutively for a little over a year now. The interface and variety of what you can sell made StockX seem like the better of all the reselling apps. It wasn't until recently when one of the packages I sent made it to them with less then what was sent in it( i.e. the shoes were removed from the box by, who knows who) that my option changed. StockX checked in to tell me the package was empty and asked for the receipt showing I sent it, also checking the weight to be sure it wasn't empty when I sent it. The package was nearing 4 pounds upon departure which the receipt verified. Come about a week later I email them again asking if anything has been found with the investigation. Long story short, they tell me they're team has looked at the package and declared it was not damaged or tampered with and that, regardless of the proof I sent them, I "never actually sent the shoes". A seller isn't given the choice to open up their own ups claim because StockX is the one paying for the shipment, so that option... isn't even an option.  They have since banned me from buying or selling, and have refused to reimburse me for the shoes I sent.

title: account was hacked; solution less than satisfactory...
reviewText: StockX gets 1 star for concept and items available, but zero stars for security, customer service, and untimely responses, as explained below.Originally, i thought it was a safe and secure app. Then, my account was hacked, email changed, shipping address changed and credit card charged. (Before you ask, i never buy anything over public or unsecured wifi.) StockX's solution was to cancel/delete my account (4 days after the fact, see below), which lead to me losing all my follows (which i'm now scrambling to remember as i was closely watching items) and portfolio. StockX did nothing to reimburse me or save my previous follows or portfolio so they could be transferred to a potentially new account. Also, it was never explained why i couldn't keep my account after the issue was spotted. Luckily, my credit card company was on top of it and took care of the charges the same day. On the other hand, it took StockX about 4 days to rectify the issue and close my account. It took about 2 days to get an initial reply, which was followed by several annoying "verifying" emails back and forth, each of which took about a day to get a reply....Given that they have a monopoly on the buyer/seller market (unless you want to pay Flight Club or GOAT prices), I'll likely be forced to reopen a new account under protest.This is a cautionary tale. Be careful, and don't link your Checking/Debit account (I'm glad i didn't). Also, if you have an issue, don't hold your breath waiting on a reply...

title: StockX stole my shoes
reviewText: I would give ZERO star if I could.  I sold a pair of Air Jordan 1 Men's sneakers through StockX, and I shipped the shoes to them for authentication verification, which is a required step throughout the selling process. I used a pre-paid UPS label provided by StockX. I put the sneakers in the package, triple-checked that everything was right. Then I took the shoes(package) to UPS. I handed it over to a UPS representative, and he gave me a receipt. The receipt clearly indicates the weight of the package is 7 pounds. 3 days later, I got an email from StockX saying that they have received the shoes and now they are under the authentication process. I waited for another 3 days, and today they sent an email to me saying my shoes didn't pass the authentication process, because I shipped an empty shoe box to them. This is absurd, I suspect the shoes were stolen internally by StockX employees, due to the high market value of the shoes. I purchased the shoes from Nike.com, for $175USD, and sold it for $1,040USD through StockX. The current market value of the shoes is above $1,100USD on StockX. So as of now, my shoes were stolen or lost at StockX, and StockX is charging me $13.95USD, and sending an empty shoe box back to me.
